<HEADLINE> S.African President Arrives in Tanzania on Working </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 26 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki arrived in Dar es Salaam Sunday for a two-day working
visit to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Mbeki who came to power in June this
year to visit Tanzania. His trip is in conjunction with the
opening ceremony of the Southern African Development Community
(SADC) Electoral Commission Forum to be held here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Both Tanzania and South Africa are members of the 14-member
SADC.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki will open the electoral forum and deliver a keynote
address.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the forum would reportedly focus on ways to
entrench democracy in the region.
</P>
<P>
The South African president will also hold talks with his host
on issues of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki was greeted by his Tanzanian counterpart Benjamin Mkapa,
Vice- President Omar Ali Juma, Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye and
other senior officials at an airport in Dar es Salaam, where
colorful artistic performances were staged.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa held a state banquet at the Sheraton Hotel in the evening
in honor of the South African president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
