<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Condemns Jewish Settlement Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Palestinian National
Authority Yasser Arafat decried on Sunday the decree of the
Israeli government to build 4,000 housing units in East Jerusalem
and the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival here from Tunisia Sunday evening, Arafat
condemned the decree as a violation of the signed agreements
between the two sides and an undermining of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Sunday, the Israeli Ministry of Construction and
Housing issued a decree to build 1,000 housing units in Adumim
settlement in East Jerusalem in addition to 2,600 apartments in
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
On the United States' role in the final status talks between
Israel and the Palestinians, Arafat said he agreed with
U.S. President Bill Clinton during their meeting in Washington on
Saturday that the U.S. will play a greater role in the last stage
of the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat had made a week-long tour of Egypt, the U.S., France and
Tunisia.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in New York, he made a speech before the United
Nations General Assembly in which he also called on Israel to
implement all signed agreements and halt expansion of Jewish
settlement in the occupied Arab territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
