<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mideast Faces Difficult Task of Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Middle East region
will face a difficult task of environment protection in the new
millennium, according to a newly-published United Nations report.
</P>
<P>
The next ten years will see pressures brought about by the
degradation of water and land resources, rapid urbanization and
industrialization and a big increase in population, said the
Geo-2000 report in a detailed chapter on the Middle East and Gulf
region.
</P>
<P>
The report was published by the United Nations Environment
Program (UNEP) and was launched Sunday in Abu Dhabi for countries
in the Middle East region.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1.2 million barrels of oil are spilled into the
Gulf annually, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Geo-2000, which was officially released in London on September
15, outlines the progress in tackling existing problems and points
to serious new threats facing the global environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
