<HEADLINE> UAE President Returns Home From Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 26 (Xinhua) -- President of the United
Arab Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan Al-Nahyan returned
home Sunday from Geneva following a private visit to Switzerland
and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Zayed usually spends the summer season in Europe where
the climate is much more pleasant than in the hot and humid UAE.
</P>
<P>
But this year, the president delayed his journey until the end
of August. The summer in the UAE starts in June.
</P>
<P>
After a few days' stay in Geneva, Sheikh Zayed left for
Cleveland, the U.S., and had medical tests there.
</P>
<P>
UAE officials dismissed U.S. newspaper reports that the
president was to have a surgery, saying the checkup was routine
and did not include surgery.
</P>
<P>
A UAE official statement later announced that the medical tests
were successful, and the president were found to be in good health.
</P>
<P>
After the checkup, Sheikh Zayed returned to his residence in
Geneva.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Zayed, who is in his 80s, underwent tests in 1998 in the
U.S. where he had a successful surgery on a vertebra in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
