<HEADLINE> Full Text of CPC Central Committee Decision (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(2) Strategically readjusting the layout of the State sector
and restructuring of SOEs. Efforts should be focused on managing
well the whole State sector, pushing forward the rational flow and
restructuring of the State assets, readjusting the lay-out and
structure of the State sector, vigorously developing large
enterprises and enterprise groups and letting medium-sized and
small SOEs to enjoy a flexible policy to invigorate themselves.
</P>
<P>
(3) Combining reforms with restructuring, remaking and
enhancement of management. In meeting demands of the market
economy, efforts should be made to transform the operational
mechanism of enterprises, enhance their overall quality, and
construct a micro-basis for industrial structure optimizing and
efficient economic operating.
</P>
<P>
(4) Establishing modern corporate systems. Efforts must be made
to achieve clearly established ownership, well-defined power and
responsibility, separation of enterprise from administration, and
scientific management, to perfect systems of decision-making,
implementation and supervision, and to make enterprises corporate
and market entities that enjoy full management authority and full
responsibility for their own profits and losses.
</P>
<P>
(5) Pushing forward scientific and technological advancement of
enterprises. Strengthen enterprise scientific research and
development as well as technical transformation, promote the
combination of enterprises, universities and research, bring into
existence systems of technological innovation, and follow the path
of intensive and sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
(6) Comprehensively enhancing enterprise management. Pursue
scientific management, intensify basic work, improve operations,
enhance efficiency, carry out diverse distribution forms with "to
each according to his work" as the main form, and establish
effective incentive and restraint mechanisms.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
