<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of CPC Central Committee Decision (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(7) Establishing a competitive mechanism of survival of the
fittest. Encourage enterprise mergers, standardize bankruptcy
procedures, divert laid-off workers, increase efficiency by
downsizing staff and encourage reemployment projects. Rely on all
forces of society to expand employment and guarantee the basic
livelihood of the SOEs' laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
(8) Coordinating the various supplementary reforms. Transform
government functions, establish well-defined power and
responsibility systems of the State assets management, supervision
and operation, and ensure that the State assets' value be
preserved and increased. Strengthen the build-up of the rule of
law, safeguard market economic orders. Improve social security
systems. Help enterprises to increase capital, lower debts and
burdens.
</P>
<P>
(9) Whole-heartedly relying on the working class and give full
play to the core role of the Party organizations within
enterprises. Strengthen enterprises' Party building-up and their
ideological and political work, upgrade qualities of managers and
administrators, uphold and improve enterprises' democratic
management system which is based on the unity of workers and staff
members, and safeguard their legitimate rights and interests in
real earnest.
</P>
<P>
(10) Promoting enterprises' ethical and cultural progress.
Intensify ideological, moral education and technical training,
comprehensively enhance the quality of workers and staff members,
cultivate positive and uplifting business environments, and
promote coordinated development of the building of a civilization
which is advanced culturally and ideologically as well as
materially.
</P>
</TEXT>
