<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi King to Return Home From Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz will return home soon from Spain, where he has been
staying since mid July, a senior Saudi official said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The king will be back to the kingdom this week, Saudi Second
Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Defense and Aviation Prince
Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz was quoted by the Saudi Press Agency as
saying. But he did not mention the specific date of Fahd's return.
</P>
<P>
Fahd, who will turn 80 soon, headed to Marbella, the Spanish
resort, on July 17 to spend the summer.
</P>
<P>
His poor health prevented him from returning home for the
funeral of his eldest son Prince Faisal Ibn Fahd, who died of
a heart attack on August 21.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi monarch has been suffering from deteriorating health
since 1995, when he was hit by a stroke.
</P>
<P>
His half-brother Crown Prince Abdullah Bin Abdul-Aziz is in
charge of the kingdom's daily affairs in the absence of the King.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
