<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of CPC Central Committee Decision (14) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is necessary to gradually establish mechanisms under which
successful enterprises can survive and loss-making enterprises are
eliminated, operators can be promoted or demoted, personnel can be
employed or fired, income can be raised or lowered, technology
continues to be upgraded, and the value of state assets are
preserved and increased.
</P>
<P>
An income distribution system compatible with the modern
enterprise system should be established, and the practice of
members of the board of the directors and the managerial ranks
receiving rewards based on their work and other contributions
should be done under the guidance of state policies.
</P>
<P>
Salary scales of workers should be determined by enterprises in
accordance with the average salaries in different localities and
the benefits of the enterprises. Within the enterprises, the
principle of distribution according to work should be followed,
but proper income gaps will be allowed. Means of production, such
as capital and technology, will be permitted to be taken into
account in distribution of profits.
</P>
<P>
Effective measures should be practiced to solve the current
problem that personal income of some monopolized industries is too
high.
</P>
<P>
Six. Strengthen and improve management of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
To intensify the management of enterprises and raise the level
of professional management is the highest need in the development
of China's modern enterprise system. It is also an important way
for state-owned enterprises to reduce financial losses and
increase profits, and to improve competitiveness.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
