<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of CPC Central Committee Decision (15) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is imperative to step up the research of development
strategies of enterprises. Enterprises should cater to the market,
draft and execute clear strategies for development, technological
innovations and marketing, and make timely adjustments in
accordance with the changes of the market.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to practice scientific and democratic decision-
making, and to keep improving the capacity for decision-making.
Risk management should be intensified to avoid major mistakes.
</P>
<P>
Various kinds of rules and systems should be improved. Basic
job duties should be intensified, and changes should be made in
situations where there are no rules to follow, no one abides by
the rules, and no one handles violations of rules.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to establish a strict responsibility system at
different levels and at different stages, and step up reviews and
supervision to make sure that responsibility is claimed for every
job.
</P>
<P>
The labor contract system should be perfected, and the practice
of encouragement through competition should be introduced.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to be strict with discipline of workers, and
rewards and penalties should be given in an impartial manner so
that workers' enthusiasm and creativity can be heightened.
</P>
<P>
Legal awareness should be enhanced, and operation and
management should be carried out according to law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of CPC Central Committee Decision (16) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A unified national accounting system should also be developed.
It is necessary that eventually there will be charts of assets and
debts, loss and profit, and cash flow in order to truly reveal the
operation state of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Earnest efforts should be made to improve economic accounting
and eliminate various loopholes. It is imperative to adhere to the
principle of "quality first," introduce advanced standards, and do
a good job of the full-process management of quality among all
workers. It is necessary to insist on treating prevention as a
primary task, and implement safety measures in production.
</P>
<P>
Attention should be paid to management, protection and rational
use of intangible assets of enterprises. It is necessary to
combine intensified management with combating corruption and
promoting honesty in work, step up auditing and supervision over
economic activities of enterprises, and to deal severely with
tampering of accounting records, violating rules regarding
financial and economic affairs, robbery and waste.
</P>
<P>
Modern management technology, methods and tools should be
widely used. It is necessary to sum up the management experiences
that have worked in the past and to refresh them with new ideas.
Management experience from advanced enterprises should be spread,
foreign talent should be imported, and modern management methods
from overseas enterprises should also be borrowed.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to bring in management specialists and provide
consulting services for enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Use of modern information technology should be strengthened,
and sensitive and accurate information systems should also be
built. It is necessary for enterprises to have rational
organizational structures, and to change those that are
overstaffed.
</P>
</TEXT>
