<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African President Leaves for SADC Meeting in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 26 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki Sunday left for Tanzania to attend a meeting of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Before departing from Waterkloof Airforce base in Pretoria,
Mbeki said the meeting of the SADC Electoral Commissions Forum
would focus on ways to entrench democracy in the region.
</P>
<P>
The forum comprising the electoral commissions of the SADC
African countries will Monday hold its annual general meeting at
which Mbeki will deliver a keynote address, South African Press
Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Presidential aide Parks Mankahlana said the meeting is
significant as it will aim to reinforce the region's commitment to
democracy and accountable governance.
</P>
<P>
It is part of a process to rid the continent of un-elected and
dictatorial governments, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki would hold discussions with Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa on a wide range of issues both sides are interested in.
</P>
</TEXT>
