<HEADLINE> Czech Republic Beats Uzbekistan 5-0 in Davis Cup Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Petr Kralert and David Rikl of
the Czech Republic sealed a 5-0 victory over Uzbekistan in Davis
Cup World Group qualifying play, trouncing Oleg Ogorodov and Vadim
Kutsenko in the doubles played in Tashkent of Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs clinched a berth in the World Group Saturday as they
took a 3-0 lead with a doubles win.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, 19-year old Kralert beat Ogorodov in straight sets 6-
3, 6-2, marking his debut for the national team.
</P>
<P>
In the second singles, David Rikl defeated Kutsenko 4-6, 6-2,6-
3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
