<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reform of State-owned Enterprises An Urgent Task </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to The Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Major
Issues Concerning the Reform and Development of State-owned
Enterprises, which was adopted at the 4th Plenum of the 15th CPC
Central Committee, the SOEs are undergoing extensive and profound
changes and the reform of the SOEs is at a critical juncture.
</P>
<P>
The Decision, issued here today, says it is imperative to adopt
practical and effective measures to solve the deep-seated problems
plaguing the SOEs, which are pillars of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The SOE reform is at the core of the whole economic reform. To
promote the development of a socialist market economy and realize
the combination of public-ownership and market economy, it is
important for the SOEs to form a management system and an
operational mechanism that meet the demands of the market economy,
the Decision points out.
</P>
<P>
It says that efforts must be made to create a new situation in
which reform, development and stability will promote one another,
the Decision stresses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
