<HEADLINE> German Rider Ullrich Wins Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Jan Ullrich of Germany
clinched the Tour of Spain on Sunday after finishing in the main
peloton on the 21st and final stage, a 163-km stage that started
and finished in the Spanish capital.
</P>
<P>
It was his second major Tour success following his victory on
the 1997 Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich was given the same time on the day as the stage winner,
Dutchman Jeroen Blijevens. 
</P>
