<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Hold Senate Election on March 4, 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government has
agreed with the National Election Commission (NEC) to hold the
senate election on March, 2000, Thailand News Agency reported on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of NEC Phirasak Kanasutra said that with the green
light from the government, his panel could smoothly prepare for
the election.
</P>
<P>
The commission had sought 1.6 billion baht (400 million U.S.
dollars) from the government to stage the election and received
1.2 billion baht from the state coffers.
</P>
<P>
The poll of the senate will be held for the first time in
Thailand according to the new constitution issued in 1997, which
stipulates that senators should be elected other than appointed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
