<HEADLINE> Ethnic Autonomous County Celebrates Founding Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people of the Tu
ethnic group today attended celebrations to mark the 45th
anniversary of the founding of their autonomous county in
northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
With a population of more than 190,000, the Tu people live
mainly in Qinghai and the southern part of Gansu Province also in
northwest China, and the Huzhu Tu Autonomous County in eastern
Qinghai, with a population of 70,000, is China's only autonomous
county for the Tu ethnic group.
</P>
<P>
The history of the Tu ethnic group dates back to the Tang
Dynasty (618-907).
</P>
<P>
The Tu people are famous for their vibrant dress, colorful
dresses, and folk dancing and singing. They live in remote rural
regions with a somewhat lagging economy. For a long time before
the founding of New China in 1949, the they were considered poor
and backward.
</P>
<P>
After 1949, especially since the country's reform and opening-
up drive started two decades ago, the group has become much more
prosperous.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the county's production value reached 458
million yuan, and total industrial and agricultural output value
reached 686 million yuan by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the county's brewing, building materials,
smelting, and power and garment-making industries have been
developing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Highlights of the celebrations, which will last for a couple of
days, include sports activities, singing and dancing contests, and
folk-custom exhibitions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
