had exhausted. He said he was determined to achieve national
progress and prosperity with the active support of people.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said he had announced 16 billion rupees of
annual development program for 1999-2000 which was in addition to
the public sector development program. Under this program, he
said, 7000 kilometer long roads from farm to market would be
completed, besides providing electricity and drinking water to the
people in rural as well as urban areas. 
