<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Cote d'Ivoire Guests (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, met with Bernard Ehui-Koutoua,
member of the Political Bureau of Democratic Party of Cote d'
Ivoire (DPCI), here today.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is also a member of the Secretariat of CPC Central
Committee, welcomed the Cote d'Ivoire guests who are visiting
China just days before the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
According to Wei, China and Cote d'Ivoire have kept frequent
high-level mutual visits and expanded friendly and cooperative
relations since the establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
"Your Prime Minister Daniel Kablan Duncan and parliament head
Emile Brou paid visits to China recently, making new efforts to
promote the growth of bilateral ties," he said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that China cherishes its traditional friendship
with Africa and is willing to bring a long-term, stable, friendly,
cooperative, and energetic Sino-African relations in all fields
well into the coming century.
</P>
<P>
Wei said China was delighted to see the stable political
situation, growing economy and improved people's life in Cote d'
Ivoire, adding that developing countries should put economic
development atop of agenda to improve their poor and backward
situation.
</P>
<P>
Wei said that China's experience demonstrates that the key to
economic development is properly handling the relationship between
reform, development and stability. "Without a stable situation, no
construction can be made," he pointed out.
</P>
