dance and other performances.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the year's World Tourism Day is the protection of
the world's cultural relics in the new century, which makes
Sichuan, home to a number of world-level cultural relics, the
proper place for China to hold the year's celebration.
</P>
<P>
The activity will call for greater efforts in China to protect
the ecological environment and natural resources in order to
promote sustainable tourism.
</P>
<P>
China has been witnessing the speedy development of tourism in
recent years, and had a more than 15 percent year-on-year rise in
foreign exchange earnings from tourism during the January-July
period this year.  
