</P>
<P>
Pallas noted that a search-and-rescue exercise will take place
off the coast of Cyprus' southwestern town of Paphos.
</P>
<P>
On October 7, the final day of the land, air and sea exercise,
military parades will take place in both Paphos and Cyprus'
southeastern town of Larnaca.
</P>
<P>
In November 1993, Cyprus and Greece agreed on a joint defense
pact, according to which Athens will offer Nicosia air, land and
sea support in case of Turkish offensive against the island.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Turkish Cypriots-controlled
north and the Greek Cypriots-dominated south since 1974 when
Turkish troops invaded and occupied the northern third of the
island in the wake of a failed coup seeking union with Athens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
