<HEADLINE> ITU to Host TELECOM 99  + INTERACTIVE 99 in October in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The International
Telecommunication Union (ITU) will host TELECOM 99 + INTERACTIVE
99 in Geneva from October 10 to 17, the United Nations agency
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda this year will be the huge growth and
influence of mobile communications and the Internet. During the
last such event in the 20th century, world leaders from the
telecom and information technology (IT) industries as well as key
figures from governments around the globe will discuss the issues
that will shape the future path of an industry already worth over
a trillion U.S. dollars in 1998.
</P>
<P>
"As the third generation mobile systems made possible by the
ITU's work on the IMT-2000 standard come into use, in the early
years of the next decade, we will finally see the dream of
anywhere anytime communications come true, for both voice and data,
" said ITU Secretary-General Yoshio Utsumi.
</P>
<P>
"But in our excitement over the apparently all-pervasive growth
of cellular telephony and the Internet," he continued, "we should
not forget that the vast majority of the world's people do not yet
have access to even basic telecommunications services. It is
essential not to create a new form of information gap between the
world's richer and poorer countries."
</P>
<P>
About 1,200 exhibitors are expected to be at the week-long
event, followed by a specially designed two-day event open to the
general public, the ITU said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
