<HEADLINE> Gold Prices Zoom UP in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices zoomed up on
the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) Monday following steep price
rise in the global market.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and 22-carat gold rose by 170 rupees (3.95 U.S.
dollars) and 160 rupees (3.72 U.S. dollars) and closed at 4,400
rupees (102.32 U.S. dollars) per ten gram and 4070 rupees (94.65
U.S. dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, ready silver (.999 fineness) hardened smartly by 85
rupees (1.98 U.S. dollars) to end at 8,200 rupees (190.70 U.S.
dollars) per kilogram from the previous close of 8,115 rupees
(188.72 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) firmed up by 90 rupees (2.09 U.S.
dollars) to 8,085 rupees (188.02 U.S. dollars) per kg. from 7,995
rupees (185.93 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
