<HEADLINE> China Improves Scholarships for Foreign Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- An official from the Ministry
of Education said today that the Chinese government improved
scholarships for foreign students studying in China on September 1.
</P>
<P>
According to a decision by the Ministries of Education and
Finance, the monthly scholarship standard for foreign
undergraduates was increased from 550 yuan (66 U.S. dollars) to
800 yuan (96 U.S. dollars), that for foreign graduates from 650
yuan (78 U.S. dollars) to 1,100 yuan (132 U.S. dollars), and that
for Ph.D. candidates from 750 yuan (90 U.S. dollars) to 1,400 yuan
(169 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Education show that 330 Chinese
universities have accepted over 310,000 foreign students from over
160 countries and regions since the People's Republic of China was
founded in 1949. Nearly 300,000 foreign students came to China in
the past two decades when the country began to implement the
policy of opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
In the past 50 years, China has offered government scholarship
to over 77,000 foreign students. Since 1990, the Chinese
government has improved scholarships for foreign students four
times.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
