<HEADLINE> China Develops Largest Offshore Oil Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and American oil
companies have jointly developed China's largest offshore oil
field, the Penglai 19-3 Oil Field in Bohai Bay, east China, which
has a theoretical oil reserve of about 300 million tons.
</P>
<P>
It is also the largest oil field jointly developed by the China
Offshore Oil Bohai Corporation (COOBC) and the Philips company of
the United States since they began cooperation in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Penglai 19-3-4 oil well that was drilled on the Penglai 19-
3 Structure recently reported a maximum daily gush of 135 tons,
indicating that the field has great potential.
</P>
<P>
Oil officials said that the development of this oil field will
help realize the goal of increasing the total oil output of the
Bohai area to 10 million tons a year in early next century.
</P>
</TEXT>
