<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetan Horse Racers Big Winners at China's National Minorities Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Horse racers from
southwestern China's Tibet Autonomous Region came out big winners
with a dominating performance at horse racing competitions at
China's on-going National Games for Traditional Sports of Minority
Nationalities in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Horse racers from the Region won the top three places of the
horseback archery event on Monday, with Tashitaje winning his
delegation's third gold medal in the competitions. Eight out of
the 18-strong field were from the Region.
</P>
<P>
Participants from Tibet Autonomous Region won the horseback
archery title at the Lhasa venue of the Games in August this year.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan minority participants took the top eight spots of
the horseback rifle shooting event here on Sunday, with
Lobsangdoje declared the champion. Racers from the Region took
half of the 20-member entries for the event.
</P>
<P>
Their closest rivals are those from the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region in the northwestern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Both events demand high skills in horse racing and shooting.
Horseback shooting, for example, allows each racer only nine
seconds to complete a 100-meter run while shooing down two
balloons placed 35 meters apart by the track. The racer who
scores more good shots in the two runs wins the event.
</P>
<P>
Experts put the long history of animal husbandry behind their
victories in the horse racing competitions. Harsh life on
horseback long ago made the ancestors of the region's herdsmen
excellent racers. Horseback racing skills had become a must to
their life for generations.
</P>
<P>
With their life much improved and incomes increased,
motorcycles and off-road vehicles are gradually replacing horses
as transportation means in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 13:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 20 Injured in Explosion in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and 20 others injured on Monday when a paint factory
exploded in Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
The strong explosion occurred at a production part of Demet
Paint Factory at Kurtkoy Sanay Street of Pendik district in
Istanbul at 14:45 local time (11:45 GMT), causing flames and the
collapse of some parts of the factory's wall.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police and fire brigade team rushed to the scene and
recovered the bodies of the two people and rescued 20 others
injured, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to hospitals for medical treatment, said
the agency.
</P>
<P>
The factory has a total of 45 workers and the casualties may
possibly increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
