<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Company Chooses HK as Asia-Pacific Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 27 (Xinhua) -- ON Semiconductor, one of
the world's leading suppliers of analog, logic and discrete
electronic component, has named Hong Kong as its Asia Pacific
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
ON Semiconductor, formerly the Semiconductor Components Group
of Motorola, is now a new and independent company.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference held this afternoon at the Grand
Hyatt to announce the decision, Steve Hanson, president of ON
Semiconductor, said that one of the reasons to choose Hong Kong as
the regional headquarters is that with its central location, Hong
Kong offers easy access to all of the company's major markets.
</P>
<P>
"Its cosmopolitan character helps us to develop new ideas and
new technology," Hanson said.
</P>
<P>
The excellent telecommunications infrastructure and its role as
the Internet traffic and content hub in Asia also lays a very good
foundation for the company to develop its e-commerce capabilities,
he added.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's unique position as a special administrative region
of China gives ON Semiconductor unparalleled advantages to open
the gateway to China's mainland," Hanson stressed.
</P>
<P>
Henry Leung, vice president and general manager for Asia
Pacific region of ON Semiconductor, said that the availability of
talents, the cost-effectiveness and the support from the local
government all help the company to choose Hong Kong as its
regional headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The company, headquartered in Phoenix, Arizona, the United
States, employs 10,000 people in Asia and runs manufacturing
plants in China, Japan, Malaysia and the Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
