<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
went up 156 HK dollars to close at 2,610 dollars a tael today,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 282.09 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 16.86 U.S. dollars up over the previous close, at today's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7665 HK dollars.
</P>
