<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Citibank Introduces New Internet Services in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Citibank Hong Kong today
announced the launch of the second generation of its Internet
financial services, which will make on-line investing easier and
more convenient.
</P>
<P>
The Internet securities services, introduced by Citibank for
the first time in the Asia-Pacific region, will offer users on-
line stock trading access with very low brokerage charges.
</P>
<P>
The key feature of the services, namely "Power Trader," allows
customers to easily visualize their transactions by viewing the
securities and settlement account status on one screen while
simultaneously checking stock prices and placing up to five stock
trading orders.
</P>
<P>
Another important feature is the "Stock Watch" service which
permits customers to preset stock watching service delivered by e-
mail. When a specific stock reaches the preset price, an e-mail
notification will be sent to the customer.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Citibank also offers on-line financial services
including credit card access, utility bill payment and mutual fund
inquiry.
</P>
<P>
William Lo, CEO of Citibank Global Consumer Banking for Hong
Kong, said Internet financial services have gained increasing
popularity and acceptance as a remote banking channel since it was
first launched last November.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, eight percent of our banking transactions are
conducted on the Internet while only 21 percent of them are
carried out at branches," Lo said. "This clearly shows the growing
importance of remote channels compared with conventional banking
methods."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
