<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Defeats South Korea 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Japan beat South Korea 1-0 in
the Under-22 international friendly soccer match here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Forward Kenji Fukuda scored the winning goal for Japan with
just nine minutes before the whistle.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Tomokazu Myojin set the stage for the goal when he
dashed deep into the right corner of the field and launched a
curving pass, which Fukuda tossed into the South Korean net in the
81st minute.
</P>
<P>
The game was the last of the two friendly matches Japan and
South Korea played in preparation for the final Asian qualifying
round for next year's Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Japan beat South Korea 4-1 in the first match, which was played
in Tokyo on September 7.
</P>
<P>
The final Asian qualifying round for next year's Sydney
Olympics starts in October in three groups.
</P>
<P>
Top teams in each group qualify for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Japan belongs to the three-team group C and South Korea to
Group B. 
</P>
</TEXT>
