<HEADLINE> Reception in Macao Marks PRC's 50th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
here today that the Chinese people have entered a new era in
building socialism with Chinese characteristics and that China
will contribute more to world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
made the remarks to more than 2,000 guests attending a grand
reception to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
At the reception hosted by the Xinhua branch, Wang first
expressed his heartfelt gratitude to those in Macao who have been
supporting the development of New China over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in half a century, China's comprehensive national
strength has been raised remarkably and the Chinese people now are
on the road to becoming well-to-do.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have shown that the Chinese people have found an
appropriate way for national development," Wang said. "Our next
goals are to achieve the nation's modernization in the mid-21st
century and contribute more to the progress of mankind."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the year of 1999 is of great significance for
the Chinese people as the PRC is 50 years old and Macao is
returning to the motherland. The two events will greatly encourage
all the Chinese to march toward the 21st century with a new
outlook."
</P>
<P>
At present, he said, Macao is in the final stage of the
transition period. The region's future chief executive has been
elected and principal officials appointed. Preparatory work for
establishing the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) is well
under way, Wang declared.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that Portugal and China can strengthen cooperation in
relevant consultations so as to ensure Macao's smooth transition
and transfer of power," he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
upcoming visit to Portugal will enhance the cooperation between
the two countries and facilitate the long-term development of
friendly bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"It is foreseeable that Macao will maintain lasting stability
and development and have a more promising future after its return
to the motherland," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira said at the reception that
the rapid economic growth China has made over the past 50 years
has laid the foundation for the country's continuous development
in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The governor expressed the wish that the Chinese people will
make even greater achievements in the future.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive of the future Macao SAR, was
also present at the reception.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
