<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian Minister Emphasizes Important Role of Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Tourism is playing an
increasingly important role in country's economy and society,
Cambodian Tourism Minister Veng Serivuth said Monday at the
Congratulation of "World Tourism Day" at Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
"Tourism has made great contributions to the increase of
government's revenue, the improvement of people's living standard
and the job creation, as well as playing an important role in
resolving regional financial crisis," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Tourist arrivals in the first six months of this year in
Cambodia recorded a 37 percent increase compared with the same
period of last year, and earned 33 million U.S. dollars for the
country while the figure in 1998 was 60 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The tourism authorities estimated that the tourism revenue this
year will increase sharply.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the important role of the tourism in promoting the
peace, friendship and economic and trade cooperation between the
countries, Veng Serivuth called on the government and local
authorities to make further efforts to maintain the political
stability and social security in order to attract more tourists.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the most promising industries in Cambodia
which boasts the centuries-old temples, such as Angkor Wat, that
are regarded as among the most magnificent monuments in the world.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
