<HEADLINE> Mubarak to Be Sworn in on October 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak will be sworn in on October 5 to serve his fourth six-year
term, a presidential decree said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The People's Assembly, Egypt's parliament, will convene that
day an extraordinary session, during which Mubarak will be sworn
in, the country's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Interior Minister Habib el-Adli announced earlier in
the day that Mubarak received about 94 percent of "Yes" votes in a
referendum Sunday on his presidency.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak became president in 1981 after the former president,
Anwar Sadat, was assassinated by Islamic radicals. He was
re-elected in 1987 and 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
