<HEADLINE> 15 Killed in Anti-Militant Operations in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 15 people, including
nine militants, were killed and four others injured since Sunday
evening as Indian army stepped up anti-militant operations in
Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said in Srinagay that Indian troops busted
six militant hideouts and recovered a huge cache of arms and
explosives, while militants abducted a person during the period.
</P>
<P>
According to PTI, two Indian soldiers lost their lives when
militants ambushed their patrol at Warpoh in Zakoora area on the
outskirts of Srinagar Monday.
</P>
<P>
Nine militants were killed in separate encounters with Indian
army as the latter stepped up anti-militant operations in frontier
district of Kupwara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
