<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Japanese Guests (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao today urged both China and Japan to continue following the
principled spirit set forth in the "Sino-Japanese Joint Statement,
" the "Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and Friendship," and the "
Sino-Japanese Joint Declaration."
</P>
<P>
Hu said that both sides should develop in-depth exchanges and
cooperation, and implement a series of important consensus and
cooperation agreements to lay a sound basis for the trans-century
development of the Sino-Japanese relationship.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made these remarks in a meeting here today with a visiting
Japanese Social Democratic Party (SDP) delegation led by its
leader Takako Doi and former Japanese prime minister Tomiichi
Murayama.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin made a successful visit to Japan last
year during which, in the spirit of learning from history and
looking toward the future, important agreement was reached
regarding the establishment of Sino-Japanese friendly cooperative
partnership devoted to peace and stability, thus mapping out the
direction for the long-term and strategic development of Sino-
Japanese relations into a new era, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
Hu also said that the successful China visit by Japanese Prime
Minister Keizo Obuchi this year reconfirmed this important
consensus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
