other senior officials of Nigerian government are currently being
compiled, underscoring the Presidency's commitment to ensuring a
corruption-free leadership for the west African country.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper, reported Monday
that a crack team of intelligence operatives, whose identities
are closely guarded, had been commissioned to compile secret
dossier on all aides of the president including permanent
secretaries and heads of extra-ministerial departments.
</P>
<P>
The assets declaration data on all public servants were being
juxtaposed with what the public servants were acquiring now, said
the paper.
</P>
<P>
The expenditure profile of all the arms of government is also
under close watch of the dossier keeper's eyes directly under the
leadership of the presidency.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian, sitting its sources, said that some of the
country's best librarians and media consultants are currently
assisting the Presidency to compile data and dossiers on
establishment matters and top government functionaries.
</P>
<P>
Some high-ranking officials and their relatives have been found
problems or even crimes by the dossier compilers.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo has been repeatedly
stating that anti-corruption is his government's top priority
since his coming into power on May 29, 1999. 
</P>
