<HEADLINE> Inland Western China Province Heading for Take-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Landlocked Shaanxi Province in
northwest China will use the country's strategic economic shift to
western parts to improve its economy, Li Jianguo, the provincial
Communist Party Committee secretary, has told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi was a revolutionary base of the Communist Party and a
sacred place of the Chinese revolution with its "Yan'an Spirit",
named for the Communist Party base, which is a combination of
diligence and working class know-how, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the twenty years of China's opening-up, however, the
province lagged behind coastal provinces because of its isolation
and late-awakening to market consciousness. But, the economy has
been given new life by the country's new infrastructure
construction and its own awareness of the need to emphasize
tourism and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The province's gross domestic product grew to 141 billion yuan
last year, 16 times the 1978 figure. During a visit to Shaanxi
this June, President Jiang Zemin told the region to take bolder
steps in the reform and opening-up, meaning that it is time to
boost the economy of the relatively backward region.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi is an important province in northwest China and has set
a goal of becoming an economic leader of the region by the year
2010, Li said. It now has the most powerful research team in the
region and has attracted specialists from various areas to join
the effort in exploring new methods of economic growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
