education and research organizations.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yongxiang, President of the Chinese Academy of Sciences,
predicted that China is expected to become the most important IT
market that witnesses fastest development. By 2003, he said, the
number of computers possessed in China will be close to 40 million,
including 37 million Internet users.
</P>
<P>
