the world of telecommunications continues to move towards wireless
technologies, which will ultimately provide users with mobile
access to all types of media and information through a number of
portable solutions, including media phones and portable computers.
</P>
<P>
Nicholas Negroponte, Co-Founder and Director of MIT Media Lab,
Massachusetts Institute of Technology, said because of a
combination of technology and culture: within the next 20 years,
the most widely-spoken language on the Internet will be Chinese,
and China will have the most advanced and digital educational
system..
</P>
<P>
Nearly 40 chairpersons and CEOs of the world IT giants,
economic experts and Chinese ministers delivered brief speeches at
the roundtable meeting.  
</P>
