<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Up Half US Cent on Gold Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar gained
half a U.S. cent Monday after one of the sharpest gold rallies
ever seen in the price of the precious metal.
</P>
<P>
The bounce in gold since its close on Friday in New York was
enough to see some analysts again predicting that the local
currency could reach 68 U.S. cents by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished the local session at 65.46 U.S.
cents, up from Friday's local close of 64.96. During the day it
traded between 65.06 and 65.6 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
In the money market Monday, the 90-day bank bill rate was at
4.98 percent from 5.01 percent and the 180-day bill was at 5.19
percent from Friday's close of 5.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Also at the local close, the Australian dollar was buying
0.6263 euro from 0.6178 at Friday's close and 68.23 Japanese yen
from 67.48. 
