<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Suffer Heavy Losses: Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan opposition
United Front Monday claimed that the ruling Taliban's troops
suffered heavy losses in recent fighting in the north of the
country, although they captured a few districts.
</P>
<P>
Opposition spokesman General Hussain Anwari said, in an email
message from Afghanistan, that a prominent Taliban commander,
Siddique, and 15 others were killed in Gordara district of
Samangan province while 70 others were captured in Imam Sahib
district of Kunduz province.
</P>
<P>
Taliban troops launched a number of offensives in Gordara and
several Kunduz districts including Sandoqzai, Dashte Archi, Imam
Sahib and Arab Quduq over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Taliban jets continued to pound the city of Taloqan,
provincial capital of Takhar, causing widespread damage and
injuries, Anwari said. 
</P>
