are individualistic rather than adherents to a strong government.
Seventy-two percent of the French polled by IFOP polling institute
said that they place more trust in individual efforts than in
government, and 59 percent support a downsizing of public work
force.
</P>
<P>
-- French Prime Ministr is expected to announce on Monday in
Strasbourg, where Socialist deputies are meeting, his measures in
support of employment. Taxing enterprises employing workers on
short-term contracts and punishing those who lay off workers while
making profits could be part of such measures. 
