<HEADLINE> Thailand Advances to Davis Cup Group I </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand earned a berth in
Davis Cup Zone Asia/Oceania Group I for the first time in eight
years after a 4-1 win over visiting Philippines in the Group II
final round Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After taking a 2-1 lead from Friday's singles and Saturday's
doubles matches, the host won the last two points from Sunday's
reversed singles through Paradorn Srichaphan and Danai Udomchoke.
</P>
<P>
The Thai No. 1 Paradorn looked a bit rusty but came alive in
time to outlast Filipino ace Brian Juinio 3-6, 6-3, 6-2, 6-7, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Danai rounded things off for Thailand when he comfortably
defeated Joseph Lizardo 6-0, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The victory means that Thailand will play in next year's Davis
Cup tennis Asia-Oceania zone Group I.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, Thailand was promoted to Group I after beating Hong
Kong of China in Group II final round. However, It went down to
India and was relegated to Group II. Since then the Kingdom has
stayed in the lower group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
