<HEADLINE> 11 Inmates Killed in Prison Riots in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and
over 30 others injured in clashes between the Turkish security
forces and political prisoners in Ankara on Sunday, local press
reported here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the incident took place when the security
forces tried to enter into wards in Ankara Main Covered Jail early
Sunday morning in a bid to search weapons and transfer the inmates
to prisons in other provinces.
</P>
<P>
The clashes between the security forces and the prisoners
lasted four hours in Ankara Prison with 11 people killed and over
30 others, including six soldiers, injured.
</P>
<P>
The bloody incident caused the prison riots spreading
throughout Turkey on Sunday, said the reports. Political prisoners
took hostage over 90 prison guards in prisons in Istanbul,
Canakkale, Cankiri, Bursa, Bartin, Aydin, Bergama and Ceyhan.
</P>
<P>
However, Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit said here on
Sunday that he had not been informed of any uprising but that he
had been told that a tunnel was being dug by the prisoners in
Ankara Prison.
</P>
<P>
The clashes began as the prisoners set up barricades and used
pistols or bottles to stop the security forces from carrying out
their mission. 
</P>
