<HEADLINE> Japan to Consider Easing Sanctions on Pyongyang: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Chief Cabinet
Secretary Hiromu Nonaka said Monday that Tokyo welcomes the recent
announcement by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
that it will freeze test-launches of long-range missiles and said
that Japan will consider easing sanctions imposed on the country.
</P>
<P>
