<HEADLINE> Simplify Equipment for Minority Nationalities' Sports, Expert Suggests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- With traditional sports of
China's minority nationalities an increasing attraction, experts
suggested to have the equipment simplified to maintain their
popularity.
</P>
<P>
"It's essential for the equipment to be more easily to make,
simpler to use and cheaper to purchase if we want to make these
sports more popular," said Wei Tiji, one of the experts in the
field in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The on-going Chinese National Games for Traditional Sports of
Minority Nationalities in Beijing feature sporting events popular
in areas with the largest communities of the 55 minority
nationalities. The largest nationality Hans covers about 91
percent of the country's total population of 1.1 billion.
</P>
<P>
"Some of the gear for traditional sports originated in Guangxi
weigh up to 1.6 tons, which has cost us a lot of money for
bringing them to Beijing," Wei said. "Some of the delegations had
even to give up some of their events due to the same problem," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The week-long Games in the Chinese capital, which opened last
Friday, had attracted 34 delegations from across the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
