<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Earns 280M Dollars From Tourism in 25 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Tourist
Corporation (PBC) has so far earned 14.01 billion taka (280
million U.S. dollar) in foreign currency during the past 25 years
when 2.66 million foreigners of different countries visited
Bangladesh, a local newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Financial Express quoted a senior official of the BPC as
saying that The BPC, since its inception in 1973, earned the
highest amount of 2.74 billion taka (54.8 million U.S. dollar) in
1997 when 182,420 foreigners visited the country.
</P>
<P>
The corporation also earned 665.1 million taka (13.5 million
U.S. dollar) from 47,008 foreign visitors in the first three
months of the current calendar year from January to March.
</P>
<P>
A senior official of the Planning Department of the BPC was
quoted as saying that the earnings from Bangladesh's tourism
sector are not significant in comparison with those from the
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
"Lack of facilities in communication system and insecurity in
different places are hampering the tourism sector in the country,"
he said, adding the government and different privately-owned
organizations should come forward to develop the tourism sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
