<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Handover Held in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The military handover was
held in Dili, capital of East Timor, on Monday morning, according
to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The handover of security command was done behind closed doors
at the military resort command in Dili following the International
Force for East Timor (Interfet)'s request that it would not be
done at the Comoro airport or by exhibiting troops.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, Maj. Gen. Kiki Syahnakri, chief of
Indonesia's Restoration Command in East Timor, handed over the
security command to Maj. Gen. Peter Cosgrove, commander of the
Interfet.
</P>
<P>
Following the handover, only one Indonesian army battalion and
combined companies of the airforce special force, marine and
mobile-brigade troops would remain in East Timor until November
when the region will be handed over to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the situation in Dili remained tense on
Sunday. Although no gunfire was heard smoke was still bellowing
from a burning Bank Danamon building.
</P>
<P>
The Interfet troops continued patrolling the city in light
armored vehicles while holding SA-80 guns, the reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
