<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Herbert Gives Stewart Their Rirst F1 Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Briton Johnny Herbert clinched
the European Grand Prix in Nuerburgring on Sunday, giving the
Stewart team its first Formula One victory.
</P>
<P>
Herbert came home 22 seconds clear of second placed Italian
Jarno Trulli driving a Prost to grab his first win since 1995 and
only the third of his career. Second place was a career best for
Trulli.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Rubens Barrichello made it a near perfect day for the
Ford-owned Stewart team, which will be re-named as Jaguar next
season, by finishing third.
</P>
<P>
World champion Mikka Hakkinen of Finland came in fifth place,
which brought the Mclaren driver two vital points and lifted him
clear of Ferrari rival Eddie Irvine in the standings. The two were
level on 60 before the race.
</P>
<P>
Irvine finished seventh behind Spaniard Marc Gene who scored
the Minardi team's first point since 1995.
</P>
<P>
Two races remain this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
