<DOCNO> XIE19990927.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Prime Minister Hails China's Achievements as Miraculous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- "The mankind has witnessed
many earth-shaking changes in the 20th century, one of the most
significant is the birth and development of the People's Republic
of China," Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai said in a
recent interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese society has been transformed from a semi-feudal,
semi-colonial agrarian base to a miraculous economy, with an
annual growth rate two and half times the world average," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"The 20 years of reform and opening-up are particularly
remarkable during which China doubled its gross domestic product
every 10 years, which would have taken 58 years in Britain, 47
years in the United States and 34 years in Japan," he said.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the great accomplishments in China's economic,
scientific-technological and cultural construction, Khai said
facts proved that the Chinese people have followed a right way of
development which has enabled it to assume an important role both
in Asia and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that the practice of the Chinese people has
offered a wise choice for other people in the world in their
efforts to build a society of fairness, love, prosperity and
happiness.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the Sino-Vietnamese relations, Khai said, "we two
peoples have been enjoying a long history of friendship and good
neighborhood. The Vietnamese people will never forget the huge
support given by the Chinese people when we were in difficulties."
</P>
<P>
He said that cooperation between the two countries has been
going well in every field, especially since the visit to China of
Vietnamese Communist Party leader Le Kha Phieu in February this
year.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two countries and two parties set forth
the principle of establishing a long-term stable, future-oriented
neighborly and all-round cooperative relationship, which will lead
the Sino-Vietnamese friendship into a new era of development, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
