<HEADLINE> S.Korea Turns in Good Show at Wrestling Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 26 (Xinhua) -- South Korea turned in an
impressive performance with a pair of golds on the last day of the
World Graeco-Roman Wrestling Championships in Peiraievs Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kim In Sub overpowered Yury Melnichenko from Kazakstan 2-0 to
clinth the 58kg category gold and his South Korean compatriot Son
Sang Pil triumphed in the 69kg class with a 4-0 win over Russian
Alexander Tretiakov.
</P>
<P>
In the 85kg category, Cuban Luis Mendez toughed out a 2-1
victory over Thomas Zander from Germany to take the gold while the
130kg-class champion turned out to be Russian Alexander Karelin,
who thrashed Hector Milian from Cuba 3-0.
</P>
<P>
China had a miserable time in the four-day tournament which
doubled as the Sydney Olympic qualifiers. A eight-strong Chinese
contingent took part in all of the eight categories but only Sheng
Zetian cracked into the top eight in the 58kg and grabbed an
Olympic berth.
</P>
<P>
Russia finished the tournament atop with Cuba coming in second
and South Korea third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
