<HEADLINE> Spurs Held 1-1 at Wimbeldon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Tottenham Hotspur missed the
chance of moving into the top six in the English premier league on
Sunday when they played a one-all at Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
Welsh target man John Hartson, a constant threat in the air,put
the home side ahead in the 57th minute with a fine downward header
at the near post.
</P>
<P>
But Spurs defender Stephen Carr levelled with 14 minutes
remaining, collecting a floated Allan Nielsen pass on the right
and firing into the roof of the net as he broke into the area.
</P>
<P>
Moments later Hartson was sent off for a second booking after
catching a defender with an arm. Tottenham captain Tim Sherwood
could have stolen the points in the final moments but blasted over
the bar.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United lead the table with 21 points from nine
matches, two clear of Leeds United and Arsenal, after they were
held 3-3 at home by Southampton on Saturday. 
</P>
