<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Beats South Africa in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain will remain in the
Davis Cup world group with a 4-1 win over South Africa in
Birmingham on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tim Henman ensured hosts' survival in the elite group next year
when he beat South African Neville Godwin 6-2, 6-2, 6-2 in the
deciding rubber of their qualifying tie.
</P>
<P>
Henman, ranked seventh in the world but with a lot to prove
since his first-round exit at the U.S. Open in August, overwhelmed
Godwin in just under two hours in the first of the reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
The result gave the home side an unbeatable 3-1 lead. Greg
Rusedski, the world number six, made the score 4-1 by beating
Grant Stafford 6-4, 7-5 in the dead rubber. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
