<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican's Fireworks Storage Exploded, Leaving 50 Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 26 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 people dead in
downtown Celaya, some 300 kilometers northwest from Mexico City
after series of explosions and a fire destroyed a section the city
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Local reports said the tragedy apparently began when a
fireworks storehouse across the street from the city bus station
exploded about 10:30 local time, starting a fire that caused
cooking gas tanks at nearby restaurants to explode a few minutes
later. The second explosion apparently trapped some rescuers who
had responded to the first blast.
</P>
<P>
Among those reported dead were a police officer, two Red Cross
workers, two fire fighters, a local reporter and four children.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican army was called in to help seal off the disaster
site and evacuate local residents. Fire fighters brought the blaze
under control by midafternoon.
</P>
<P>
So far, the explosion caused at least 50 people dead and 76
wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
